      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been watching the pigeons in the park for the last three weeks and i realized they arent just hanging out. they're actually signaling weather changes through these specific flight patterns. like, when they do these rapid circular loops before settling, it always precedes a drop in pressure and rain within like 2 hours. it's actually pretty intense how clear it is once you see it. has anyone else ever noticed this or am i the only one seeing the pattern?",
